on\n|-\n| March 30, 1960\n| [[Alice, Texas]], United States\n| Donna Dvorak, 14\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Donna Dvorak, 14, brought a target pistol to Dubose Junior High School, and fatally shot Bobby Whitford, 15, in their 9th grade science class.  Dvorak believed Whitford posed a threat to one of her girlfriends.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=jthHAAAAIBAJ&sjid=IoAMAAAAIBAJ&pg=3467,122520&dq=dvorak&hl=en|work=The Victoria Advocate|title=Youth Fatally Shot In Crowded Class|date=Mar 31, 1960}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 4, 1961\n| [[Kung\u00e4lv]], [[Sweden]] \n| Ove Conry Andersson, 17\n| 1 dead\n| 6 injured\n| |[[Kung\u00e4lv school shooting]]. A 17-year-old student fired fifteen bullets into a crowd at a school dance at Kung\u00e4lvs L\u00e4roverk (a/k/a Thorildskolan), killing one student and wounding six others before escaping. He turned himself in to local police the following morning and was arrested.\n|-\n| October 17, 1961\n| [[Denver, Colorado]], United States\n| Tennyson Beard, 14\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| Tennyson Beard, 14, got into an argument with William Hachmeister, 15, at Morey Junior High School. During the argument Beard pulled out a revolver and shot at Hachmeister, wounding him. Deborah Faith Humphrey, 14, was fatally wounded by another shot. Beard was arrested after fleeing the school.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=PAozAAAAIBAJ&sjid=w-cDAAAAIBAJ&pg=4617,710365 |title=School Fight Mushrooms Into Murder |publisher=News.google.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 26, 1962\n| [[Taipei]], [[Taiwan]]\n| Tsui Yin, 41\n| 7 dead\n| 3 injured\n| Tsui Yin, a 41-year-old former physical education teacher at Li Shing Junior High School in Taipei, shot and killed the principal, the principal's wife and five other faculty members with a pistol, in revenge for his dismissal. He wounded three others, among them the principal's daughter, before escaping in a taxi. He was arrested and sentenced to death.<ref>Admits killing 7 for revenge, ''[[Pacific Stars and Stripes]]'' (January 27, 1962)</ref><ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=H2gUAAAAIBAJ&sjid=KQEEAAAAIBAJ&pg=7282,775520&dq= Teacher who slew 7 denied wish to see pupil perform], ''[[Toledo Blade]]'' (July 26, 1962)</ref>\n|-\n|May 7, 1963\n|[[Paterson, New Jersey]]\n|Ralph Best, 43\n|\n|6 injured\n|Gun engraver Ralph Best opened fire from his second floor room with a .22 caliber hunting rifle on 50 children playing in the schoolyard at Paterson School 14, on the evening of May 7, 1963. An alcoholic and epileptic, he fired after the children ignored his demands they leave the playground. Charged with \"atrocious assault\", Best pled insanity. His first trial ended in a mistrial, and he was never re-tried.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.northjersey.com|title=An oft-forgotten school shooting|last=Maag|first=Christopher|date=January 21, 2019|work=The Record|access-date=|page=1A}}</ref>\n|-\n| April 27, 1966\n| [[Bay Shore, New York]], United States\n| James Arthur Frampton, 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Teacher John S. Lane, 48, was shot and fatally wounded when he tried to stop 16-year-old student James Arthur Frampton, who was walking with a shotgun in the high school, seeking students with whom he had argued. Lane died of his wounds on June 13, 1966.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1966/04/28/archives/li-teacher-shot-by-boy-in-school-badly-wounded-trying-to-halt.html L.I. teacher shot by boy in school], ''The New York Times'' (April 28, 1966)</ref><ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1966/04/29/archives/li-boy-held-in-shooting-faces-psychiatric-exam.html L.I. Boy Held in Shooting Faces Psychiatric Exam], ''The New York Times'' (April 29, 1966)</ref><ref>[https://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=FB0B1FFD3559137B93C6A8178DD85F428685F9 Teacher Shot by Youth Dies in Bay Shore Hospital], ''[[The New York Times]]'' (June 14, 1966)</ref>\n|-\n| October 5, 1966\n| [[Grand Rapids, Minnesota]], United States\n| David M. Black Jr., 15\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| David Black, a 15-year-old student at [[Grand Rapids High School]], took a pistol to school - shooting student Kevin Roth and administrator Forrest L. Willey, with whom he had argued. Willey died of his wound eight days later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.columbine-angels.com/grand_rapids_high.htm |title=A wound still fresh//The survivor of a 1966 school shooting in Minnesota is still coming to grips with the pain \u2013 and with his own role in the tragedy |publisher=Columbine-angels.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 26, 1967\n| [[Dayton, Ohio]], United States\n| Will Edward Dixon, 19\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Thomas Prinz, a 21-year-old football coach at Wilbur Wright High School, was stabbed to death by 19-year-old Will Edward Dixon. The stabbing occurred when Prinz attempted to escort Dixon off the playing field. Dixon was a former student and drop-out from the school.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=iJYuAAAAIBAJ&sjid=IUgDAAAAIBAJ&pg=5062,4240840&dq=school+stabbing+death&hl=en |title=Dayton Coach Stabbed To Death By Youth |publisher=News.google.ca |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| November 1, 1967\n| [[Dundee]], [[Scotland]], United Kingdom\n| [[Robert Mone]], 19\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 19-year-old soldier Robert Mone entered [[St John's RC High School]] armed with a shotgun and took a class hostage. He sexually abused the children. The teacher, Nanette Hanson, convinced Mone, who had already raped one girl, to let the children go. Mone fatally shot her in the head. Mone had been expelled three years before, and was apparently seeking revenge; he was found to be insane and sent to the [[State Hospital]] in [[Carstairs]].<ref>[http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/scottish-news/2007/11/02/tribute-to-teacher-killed-by-monster-mone-86908-20049591/ Tribute To Teacher Killed By Monster Mone], ''[[Daily Record (Scotland)|Daily Record]]'' (November 2, 2007)</ref>\n|-\n| January 30, 1968\n| [[Miami]], [[Florida]], United States\n| Blanche Patricia Ward, 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 16-year-old Blanche Ward shot and killed fellow 16-year-old student, Linda Lipscomb, with a pistol at Miami Jackson High School. According to Ward, she was threatened with a razor by Lipscomb during an argument and in the ensuing struggle her gun went off.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=vBoMAAAAIBAJ&sjid=vlwDAAAAIBAJ&pg=4031,176485&dq= Fatal shooting brings action], ''[[St. Petersburg Times]]'' (February 1, 1968)</ref>\n|-\n| March 25, 1968\n| [[High Point, North Carolina]],  United States\n| Gerald Locklear, 16\n| 1 dead\n| \n| David Walker, 15, was shot to death just outside Central High School by Gerald Locklear, 15.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1314&dat=19680326&id=j7VWAAAAIBAJ&sjid=gOkDAAAAIBAJ&pg=5447,3659292&hl=en Student Held In Slaying], ''[[The Spokesman-Review]]'' (March 26, 1968)</ref>\n|-\n| May 22, 1968\n| [[Miami]], [[Florida]], United States\n| Ernest Lee Grissom, 15\n|\n| 2 injured\n| Ernest Lee Grissom, a 15-year-old student at Drew Junior High School, shot and seriously wounded a teacher and a 13-year-old student after he had been reprimanded for a disturbance.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=i-MTAAAAIBAJ&sjid=SQUEAAAAIBAJ&pg=2587,3245401&dq= Teacher, student serious following shooting by youth], ''[[Ocala Star-Banner]]'' (May 23, 1968)</ref>\n|-\n| November 19, 1969\n| [[Tomah, Wisconsin]], United States\n| ..., 14\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Principal Martin Mogensen is shot to death in his office by a 14-year-old boy armed with a [[shotgun]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.madison.com/wsj/spe/Weston/index.php?ntid=101225 |title=Some other incidents involving guns at Wisconsin schools |publisher=Madison.com |date=2011-02-15 |accessdate=2011-03-12 }}{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1314&dat=19691120&id=JUIVAAAAIBAJ&sjid=HAgEAAAAIBAJ&pg=5900,1913651 |title=Shots Kill High School Principal |publisher=News.google.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===1970s===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:65px;\"| Date\n! style=\"width:85px;\"| Location\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Attacker(s)\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" style=\"width:75px;\"| Dead{{r|group=lower-alpha|note_a}}\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" style=\"width:75px;\"| Injured{{r|group=lower-alpha|note_a}}\n! Description\n|-\n| January 5, 1970\n| [[Washington, District of Columbia]], United States\n| Unnamed student\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| Tyrone Perry, 15, was shot to death and a 14-year-old boy was wounded at Hine Junior High School.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=AfRYAAAAIBAJ&sjid=cOsDAAAAIBAJ&pg=3025,1894998&dq=boy+shot+at+school&hl=en|work=The Spokesman-Review|title=Boys Hurt, Killed In Shootings|date=January 6, 1970}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 1, 1971\n| [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]], United States\n| Kevin Simmons, 14\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Samson L. Freedman, a 56-year-old art teacher, was shot to death by Kevin Simmons at Leeds Junior High School, after having the student suspended for cursing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1971/02/02/archives/art-teacher-slain-philadelphia-police-arrest-youth-14.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923170859/http://www.nytimes.com/1971/02/02/archives/art-teacher-slain-philadelphia-police-arrest-youth-14.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=23 September 2016|title=Art Teacher Slain; Philadelphia Police Arrest Youth, 14 \u2013 The New York Times|date=23 September 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| November 3, 1971\n| [[Carlsbad, New Mexico]],\nUnited States\n| Michael O'Hearn, 22\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| Michael O'Hearn barricaded himself in a storage tower of Carlsbad Mid-High School, in [[Carlsbad, New Mexico]], for about two hours with two firearms. He fired about two dozen rounds at police officers, injuring one, before committing suicide.<ref name=\"stpetersburg110471\">{{cite news|title=Sniper's Victim: Himself|date=1971-11-04|url =https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=k9IMAAAAIBAJ&sjid=tWADAAAAIBAJ&pg=3115,1900854&|work=[[St. Petersburg Times]]|accessdate = 2009-04-18}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 24, 1972\n| [[Stow, Ohio]], United States\n| \n|\n| 1 injured\n| A 16-year-old student at Stow High School shot and wounded his chemistry teacher during an argument.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=dk8LAAAAIBAJ&sjid=a1IDAAAAIBAJ&pg=5155,1313401&dq= Youth shoots chem teacher], ''[[The Bryan Times]]'' (January 25, 1972)</ref>\n|-\n| January 7\u201312, 1973\n| [[Balassagyarmat]], Hungary\n| Andr\u00e1s Pintye, 18 and L\u00e1szl\u00f3 Pintye, 17\n| 1 dead\n| Several hostages required medical attention\n| Brothers Andr\u00e1s and L\u00e1szl\u00f3 Pintye, sons of local Communist Party officials, have acquired a [[FEG PA-63|PA-63]] pistol and an [[AMD-65|AMD]] assault rifle and assaulted a local girls' dormitory. They held an unknown number of teenage girls hostage for several days, demanding free passage to Budapest's international airport and a flight to Austria. Finally, when they planned to murder some of the hostages, a police sniper shot Andr\u00e1s dead through the window, then the police stormed the building, arresting L\u00e1szl\u00f3. He was sentenced to 15 years of prison, from which he was released in 1984, serving a little more than 11 years. Four other persons were sentenced for aiding the perpetrators. The case deeply traumatized Hungary which has never seen such events before. A feature film titled T\u00faszt\u00f6rt\u00e9net (Hostage Story) was made about the events in 1989.<ref>[[:hu:Balassagyarmati t\u00faszdr\u00e1ma#A t.C3\u00baszdr\u00e1ma ut\u00f3\u00e9lete|Wikipedia (Hungarian) article about the hostage drama]]</ref>{{Circular reference|date=May 2017}}\n|-\n| February 26, 1973\n| [[Richmond, Virginia]], United States\n|\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Wayne Phillips, 17, was shot to death when he was caught between two youths who were fighting in the hallway of [[Armstrong High School (Richmond, Virginia)|Armstrong High School]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=CTJgAAAAIBAJ&sjid=s28NAAAAIBAJ&pg=4009,6506820&dq=boy+killed+at+school&hl=en |newspaper=The Phoenix|title=Boy Killed In Gun Battle|date=February 27, 1973}}</ref>\n|-\n| July 1973\n|\n|\n|\n|\n| In the [[attack on St Alberts School]], [[Zimbabwe African National Liberation Army]] (ZANLA) cadres captured 292 pupils and staff from the school and [[death march|force-marched]] them north towards [[Mozambique (Portugal)|Mozambique]], where the ZANLA bases were. The march was intercepted by the [[Rhodesian Security Forces]] before the cadres crossed the border, and all but eight of the children and staff were recovered.<ref>{{cite book|title=Counter-Insurgency in Rhodesia|last=Cilliers|first=Jackie|location=London, Sydney & Dover, New Hampshire|publisher=Croom Helm|date=December 1984|isbn=978-0-7099-3412-7|page=18}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 2, 1974\n| [[San Luca]], Italy\n|\n| 1 dead\n|\n| A student shot and killed his teacher, Silvio Strangio, after he had been reprimanded for distracting his classmates.<ref>[http://hemeroteca.abc.es/nav/Navigate.exe/hemeroteca/madrid/abc/1974/02/03/033.html Mata a su profesor en clase], ''[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]'' February 3, 1974</ref>\n|-\n| March 22, 1974\n| [[Brownstown, Indiana]], United States\n| \n| 1 dead\n|\n| Jessie Blevins, 48, athletic director at Brownstown Central High School, was shot to death in the school parking lot by a 17-year-old student.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=W3dQAAAAIBAJ&sjid=fxEEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6244,1615348&dq=boy+killed+at+school&hl=en |newspaper=The Milwaukee Sentinel|title=Pupil Shoots, Kills Athletic Director|date=March 23, 1974}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 30, 1974\n| [[Olean, New York]], United States\n| Anthony Barbaro, 17\n| 3 dead\n| 11 injured\n| [[Olean High School shooting]]. 17-year-old student Anthony Barbaro indiscriminately shot at people on the street from windows at the third floor of the school building. He killed three people and wounded 11 before police managed to subdue him.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=vQ4LAAAAIBAJ&sjid=-VEDAAAAIBAJ&pg=3163,7727175&dq=anthony+barbaro+regent Teen sniper kills three, 11 wounded, ''The Bryan Times''] (December 31, 1974)</ref>\n|-\n| March 18, 1975\n| [[St. Louis, Missouri]], United States\n| \n| 1 dead\n| \n| 16-year-old Stephen Goods, a bystander, is shot and killed during a fight between other teens at [[Sumner High School (St. Louis)|Sumner High School]].<ref name=\"PAC\">{{cite web | url=http://policeacademyu.com/school-violence/ | title=Facts about school violence in the U.S. |publisher=policeacademyu.com | accessdate=December 12, 2014 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141214212942/http://policeacademyu.com/school-violence/ | archivedate=December 14, 2014 }}</ref>\n|-\n| May 28, 1975\n| [[Brampton, Ontario]], Canada\n| Michael Slobodian, 16\n| 3 dead\n| 13 injured\n| [[Centennial Secondary School shooting]]. Michael Slobodian, 16, killed a teacher and student and wounded 13 others at Brampton Centennial Secondary School in Brampton, Ontario, before fatally shooting himself.\n|-\n| September 11, 1975\n| [[Oklahoma City, Oklahoma]], United States\n| James Briggs, 15\n| 1 dead\n| 5 injured\n| Grant High School student Randy Truitt was shot and killed by James Briggs at the school, who also wounded several others.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=pFVOAAAAIBAJ&sjid=yPgDAAAAIBAJ&pg=3249%2C2241230 |title=Charge Filed in Shooting |work=[[Spokane Daily Chronicle]] |date=September 24, 1975 |accessdate=January 16, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 27, 1975\n| [[Ottawa]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| [[Robert Poulin]], 18\n| 3 dead\n| 5 injured\n| [[St. Pius X High School shooting]]. 18-year-old Robert Poulin opened fire on his class with a shotgun at [[St. Pius X High School (Ottawa)|St. Pius X High School]], killing one and wounding five before turning the gun on himself. Poulin had raped and stabbed his 17-year-old friend Kim Rabot to death prior to the shooting.\n|-\n| February 12, 1976\n| [[Detroit]], [[Michigan]], United States\n| \n| \n| 5 injured\n| Intruders shot five Murray-Wright High School students after an apparent dispute over one of the intruder's girlfriends.<ref name=wound5>\"[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=LQ9PAAAAIBAJ&sjid=dgIEAAAAIBAJ&pg=3947,2156747&dq=murray-wright-high-school&hl=en Intruders Wound 5 Students In Shooting At Detroit School]\". ''[[Associated Press]]'' at the ''[[Toledo Blade]]''. Friday February 13, 1976 (141st year). Page 2. Retrieved from [[Google Books]] (3 of 20) on November 2, 2012.</ref>\n|-\n| April 7, 1977\n| [[Whitharral, Texas]], United States\n| Ricardo Lopez, 17\n| 1 dead\n|\n| High School principal M. O. Tripp was shot to death on the front steps of the school by Ricardo Lopez, 17.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=REAhAAAAIBAJ&sjid=_1EDAAAAIBAJ&pg=5618,677358&dq=tripp&hl=en|work=The Bryan Times|title=Police Don't Know Reason Student Killed His Principal|date=Apr 7, 1977}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 12, 1977\n| [[Winter Garden, Florida]], United States\n| Roosevelt Holloman, 41\n| 1 dead\n|\n| During an after-school meeting at West Orange High School to discuss his illegal advances toward a 16-year-old girl, 41-year-old assistant principal Roosevelt Holloman pulled out a gun and shot principal Raymond Screws, 51, to death. Holloman also shot at two other school officials but missed. Holloman surrendered his gun to a janitor and waited until being arrested. He was later convicted of [[first-degree murder]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=888&dat=19771213&id=N-8LAAAAIBAJ&sjid=HVoDAAAAIBAJ&pg=3129,4205065 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120723175746/http://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=888&dat=19771213&id=N-8LAAAAIBAJ&sjid=HVoDAAAAIBAJ&pg=3129,4205065 |url-status=dead |archive-date=2012-07-23 |title=Principle (sic) shot to death |publisher=News.google.com |date=1977-12-13 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1346&dat=19771213&id=ZnUsAAAAIBAJ&sjid=o_oDAAAAIBAJ&pg=6331,2860961 |title=School Principle (sic) Shot to Death |publisher=News.google.com |date=1977-12-13 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=5gMMAAAAIBAJ&sjid=g1oDAAAAIBAJ&pg=3946,830644&dq=principal+shot+screws+kissed&hl=en |title=Slayer of school principal convicted of first-degree murder |publisher=News.google.ca |date=1978-06-10 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 4, 1978\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| Everton Lazarus, 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Michael Kittrell, 15, was stabbed to death by another student at John Adams High School.<ref>{{cite news|author=[ Displaying Abstract ] |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1978/02/03/archives/youth-is-arrested-in-students-killing.html |title=Youth Is Arrested In Student's Killing |publisher=Select.nytimes.com |date=2011-03-02 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 22, 1978\n| [[Lansing, Michigan]], United States\n| Roger Needham, 15\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| Roger Needham, a 15-year-old student, shot two students at Everett High School. One of the students, 15-year-old Bill Draher, died of his gunshot wound.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kresnak |first=Jack |url=http://www.justicejournalism.org/crimeguide/chapter02/chapter02_pg02.html |title=Juvenile Justice |publisher=Justicejournalism.org |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 18, 1978\n| [[Austin, Texas]], United States\n| John Daniel Christian, 13\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 13-year-old honor student John Christian, son of former LBJ press secretary [[George Christian (journalist)|George Christian]], fatally shot his teacher, 29-year-old Rod Grayson, three times at Murchison Junior High School. Christian fled the school building and was subdued by gym coach Larry Schirpik. Christian's attorney, Roy Minton, argued Christian was [[Insanity defence|not guilty by reason of insanity]], and district attorney Ronnie Earle did not object. The case did not go to trial. Christian was treated for two years at a private mental health facility in Dallas paid for by his family.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.michaelcorcoran.net/archives/1469 |title=Austin\u2019s Secret: Killing in the Classroom 1978 |publisher=MichaelCorcoran.net |accessdate=2012-12-17}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 1978\n| [[Winnipeg, Manitoba]], Canada\n| Vaughan Pollen, 17\n| 1 dead\n|\n| A 16-year-old student, Kenneth Maitland, was shot to death with a shotgun by 17-year-old student, Vaughan Pollen, at Sturgeon Creek Regional Secondary School. Pollen was charged with murder but during the trial found unfit to stand trial by reason of a mental disorder. He was committed to a mental health facility for treatment of [[paranoid schizophrenia]] and treated for 7 years.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/background/school-shootings/ |title=Attacks on students and staff |publisher=Cbc.ca |date=2008-09-23 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100130091329/http://www.cbc.ca/news/background/school-shootings/ |archivedate=January 30, 2010 }}</ref>\n|-\n| January 29, 1979\n| [[San Diego, California]], United States\n| Brenda Spencer\n| 2 dead\n| 9 injured\n| A 16-year-old student, Brenda Spencer, began shooting from her home at children who were waiting outside Cleveland Elementary School for principal Burton Wragg (aged 53) to open the gates. She injured eight children. Wragg was killed while trying to help the children. Custodian Mike Suchar (aged 56) was killed while trying to pull a student to safety. Asked by a reporter why she committed the crime, Spencer is said to have replied \"[[I Don't Like Mondays]]\"\n|}\n\n===1980s===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:65px;\"| Date\n! style=\"width:85px;\"| Location\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Attacker(s)\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" style=\"width:75px;\"| Dead{{r|group=lower-alpha|note_a}}\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" style=\"width:75px;\"| Injured{{r|group=lower-alpha|note_a}}\n! Description\n|-\n| January 7, 1980\n| [[Stamps, Arkansas]], United States\n| Evan Hampton, 16\n| 1 dead\n| \n| Evan Hampton, 16, high school freshman student at Stamps High School, shot Mike Sanders, 19, twice in the chest and once in the temple, killing him instantly. He was arrested.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=799&dat=19800109&id=0CccAAAAIBAJ&sjid=41cEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6542,692754|newspaper=The Bryan Times|title=Death of student makes no sense|date=January 9, 1980}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 31, 1980\n| [[Hueytown, Alabama]], United States\n| Rudy Farmer, 17\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| 17-year-old Rudy Farmer pulled out a pistol and shot a fellow student in the art room at Hueytown High School.  That student was wounded.  Farmer fatally shot himself.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1454&dat=19801101&id=CcgsAAAAIBAJ&sjid=RRMEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6542,12997|newspaper=The Star-News|title=Student killed in school shooting|date=November 1, 1980}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 2, 1981\n| [[Greenville, South Carolina]], United States\n| Jewel Loraine Garrett, 18\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Henry Chiariello, a 30-year-old social studies teacher, was stabbed to death at Greenville High School by 18-year-old student Jewel Garrett. Garrett was later sentenced to life in prison.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=KnQQAAAAIBAJ&sjid=m4sDAAAAIBAJ&pg=5899,421593&dq=henry+chiariello |title=Slain |publisher=News.google.com |date=1981-10-03 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 12, 1982\n| [[Miami, Florida]], United States\n| Steven Wayne Holmes, 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Francisco Walker, 24, a sixth-grade teacher at Edison Middle School, was stabbed to death by a teenaged trespasser, 15-year-old Steven Wayne Holmes. He was later arrested and charged with first degree murder.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=kNMRAAAAIBAJ&sjid=h-4DAAAAIBAJ&pg=6038,4608633&dq=school+stabbing+death&hl=en |title=Teacher stabbed to death |publisher=News.google.ca |date=1982-01-13 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=WOgTAAAAIBAJ&sjid=EwYEAAAAIBAJ&pg=5606,5408156&dq=francisco+walker&hl=en |title=15-Year-Old Arrested In Slaying Of Teacher |publisher=News.google.ca |date=1982-01-13 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 19, 1982\n| [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]], United States\n| Pat Lizotte, 17\n| 1 dead\n| 3 injured\n| Clarence Piggott, a 55-year-old psychology and sociology teacher, was shot to death, and two students were wounded by a high school senior. The student was later shot and wounded by police before arrest.<ref>{{cite news|author=AP |url=https://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F30911FB3D5D0C738EDDAA0894DA484D81 |title=The New York Times Article March 20, 1982 |location=Las Vegas (Nev) |publisher=Select.nytimes.com |date=1982-03-20 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=FLQSAAAAIBAJ&sjid=YvkDAAAAIBAJ&pg=6010,1797067&dq= Shooting spree], ''[[Spokane Chronicle]]'' (March 22, 1982)</ref> Lizotte is sentenced to two consecutive life sentences without the possibility of parole. However, he was granted parole on March 6, 2017 after a Nevada law banning life without parole for juveniles reduced his sentence to 20 years to life.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news3lv.com/news/local/student-convicted-in-1982-shooting-death-of-valley-hs-teacher-granted-parole|title=Student convicted in 1982 shooting death of Valley HS teacher granted parole|last=Garcia|first=John Treanor and Tony|work=KSNV|access-date=2017-07-06|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|-\n| April 7, 1982\n| [[Littleton, Colorado]], United States\n| [[1982 Deer Creek Shooting|Jason Rocha]], 14\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Jason Rocha, a 14-year-old student, shot and killed 13 year-old Scott Darwin Michael, a fellow student at [[Deer Creek Middle School]] in Littleton, Colorado. Rocha was charged as an adult and sentenced to 12-years in prison for the murder.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1876&dat=19840304&id=U0IsAAAAIBAJ&sjid=rM4EAAAAIBAJ&pg=5024,759361 |title=These Kids Are \u2018Middle-Class Murderers |publisher=News.google.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 20, 1983\n| [[St. Louis County, Missouri]], United States\n| David F. Lawler, 14\n| 2 dead\n| 1 injured\n| 14-year-old David F. Lawler took two family pistols to school and shot two classmates, killing one and injuring the other. In a murders/suicide note he had brought with him, he outlined his intention to kill the next person heard speaking ill of his older brother Ken. He entered a study hall classroom and opened fire, hitting the two victims. The first was fatally shot in the stomach, and the second received a non-fatal gunshot wound to the abdomen. After, he said, \"no one will ever call my brother a pussy again\". He then committed suicide. See [[Parkway South Junior High School shooting|Parkway South Junior High School killings]] for more information.\n|-\n| May 16, 1983\n| [[Dallas, Texas]], United States\n| Billy Conn Gardner\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Billy Conn Gardner, a friend of a food service worker's husband, robbed the [[Lake Highlands High School]] cafeteria at gunpoint, shot the food service director, and left with $1,600. The food service director, Thelma Row, died eleven days later from the injuries. Gardner was later apprehended, convicted, and sentenced to death via Lethal Ejection for the crime. The State of Texas executed him on February 16, 1995.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://lakehighlands.advocatemag.com/2014/03/history-shooting-lake-highlands-cafeteria-worker-remembered/|author=Toler, Carol|title=History: Shooting of Lake Highlands cafeteria worker remembered|date=2014-03-04|accessdate=2018-04-26|publisher=Advocate Magazine (Lake Highlands)}}</ref>\n|-\n| June 3, 1983\n| [[Eppstein|Eppstein-Vockenhausen]], Germany\n| Karel Charva, 34\n| 6 dead\n| 14 injured\n| [[Eppstein school shooting]]. Thirty-five-year-old [[Czechs|Czech]] [[refugee]] Karel Charva, fatally shot three students, a teacher and a police officer, and injured another 14 people with two [[semi-automatic pistol]]s, before committing [[suicide]] at the [[Heinrich Friedrich Karl vom und zum Stein|Freiherr-vom-Stein]] [[Gesamtschule]].<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1983/06/04/world/around-the-world-classroom-gun-rampage-leaves-6-germans-dead.html Classroom Gun Rampage Leaves 6 Germans Dead], ''[[The New York Times]]'' (June 4, 1983)</ref>\n|-\n| December 16, 1983\n| [[Rockford, Illinois]], United States\n| Michael Graham, 15\n|\n| 1 injured\n| Michael Graham, a 15-year-old student at Boylan Central Catholic High School, shot and wounded his German teacher, Sharon Mundt, who had disciplined him for misbehavior.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=uSEVAAAAIBAJ&sjid=UwYEAAAAIBAJ&pg=3636,1012288&dq= Student's threat to shoot teacher was dismissed by classmates as joke], ''[[Ocala Star-Banner]]'' (December 18, 1983)</ref>\n|-\n| March 13, 1984\n| [[Castres]], France\n| \n| 2 dead\n|\n| A 15-year-old student killed his teacher, who had sent him to the headmaster for being late, and shot himself in the head. He died on the way to the hospital.<ref>[http://suche.abendblatt.de:8000/article.php?xmlurl=http://87.230.59.37/ha/1984/xml/19840314xml/habxml840103_9060.xml&pdfurl=http://87.230.59.37/ha/1984/pdf/19840314.pdf/ASV_HAB_19840314_HA_032.pdf Lehrer erschossen]{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, ''[[Hamburger Abendblatt]]'' (March 14, 1984)</ref>\n|-\n|September 4, 1985\n|[[Richmond, Virginia]], United States\n| Student, 12-years-old\n| 1 dead\n|\n| At the end of the second day of school at East End Middle School, a 12-year-old boy shot a girl with his mother's gun. <ref> https://www.k12academics.com/school-shootings/history-school-shootings-united-states}</ref>\n|-\n| October 18, 1985\n| [[Detroit]], [[Michigan]], United States\n| Suspect\n| \n| 6 injured\n| During halftime of the homecoming football game between [[Northwestern High School (Michigan)|Northwestern]] and [[Murray-Wright High School|Murray-Wright]], a boy who had been in a fight earlier that day retaliated with a shotgun, wounding six students.<ref>{{cite news |newspaper=[[Houston Chronicle]] |title=6 Shot, Injured at Homecoming|url=https://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl/1985_45387/6-shot-injured-at-homecoming.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |newspaper=Houston Chronicle |title=Fight Occurred At School Before Shootings|url=https://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl/1985_45930/fight-occurred-at-school-before-shootings.html}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 3, 1985\n| [[Concord, New Hampshire]], United States\n| Louis Cartier, 16\n| 1 dead\n| \n| At [[Concord High School (New Hampshire)|Concord High School]], Louis \"Louie\" Cartier, a 16-year-old male dropout, entered the school with a shotgun and took two students hostage. Responding officers fatally shot him as he aimed at a teacher.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p0qPt8jUr7E&t=9m|title=ABC News Nightline, Jan 29, 1986 \u2013 Challenger disaster one month after fatal school shooting|work=YouTube|accessdate=October 1, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Sarah Chalsma |url=http://www.concordmonitor.com/home/3438627-95/1985-concord-shooting-believe |title=My Turn: In 1985, Concord High was the site of another school shooting |publisher=concordmonitor.com |date=2012-12-19 |accessdate=January 14, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150627164824/http://www.concordmonitor.com/home/3438627-95/1985-concord-shooting-believe |archivedate=June 27, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Tom Mooney |url=http://www.apnewsarchive.com/1985/Wounded-Teen-Dies-Day-After-Police-Shots-Ended-Hostage-Incident/id-af067d94a4e319a31af445ae0190dcff |title=Wounded Teen Dies Day After Police Shots Ended Hostage Incident |agency=Associated Press |date=1985-12-04 |accessdate=January 14, 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 10, 1985\n| [[Portland, Connecticut]], United States\n| Floyd Warmsley, 13\n| 1 dead\n| 2 injured\n| 13-year-old student Floyd Warmsley fatally shot a school custodian, wounded both the principal and school secretary, and held a student hostage with an assault pistol at Portland Junior High School in [[Portland, Connecticut]] - after he had been suspended for a minor issue. His aunt convinced him to surrender.<ref name=\"atlanta121185\">{{cite news|title=Junior-high student, 13, arrested after shooting death at school|date=1985-12-11|url =http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=AT&p_theme=at&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB7C1D85565E733&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM|work=[[The Atlanta Journal-Constitution]]|accessdate = 2009-04-18}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 6, 1986\n| [[Dolton, Illinois]], United States\n| Student, 14\n|\n| 1 injured\n| A 14-year-old student shot and wounded his math teacher at [[Thornridge High School]].<ref>[https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/chicagotribune/access/24994037.html?dids=24994037:24994037&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&date=Mar+07%2C+1986&author=Andrew+Bagnato+and+Andrew+Fegelman&pub=Chicago+Tribune+(pre-1997+Fulltext)&desc=SUBURB+TEEN+SHOOTS+TEACHER+AT+SCHOOL&pqatl=google Suburb teen shoots teacher at school], ''[[Chicago Tribune]]'' (March 7, 1986)</ref><ref>[http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=CSTB&p_theme=cstb&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB36CF4D1CAABF7&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM Dolton cops hold gun-wielding boy], ''[[Chicago Sun-Times]]'' (March 7, 1986)</ref>\n|-\n| October 8, 1986\n| [[Dallas, Texas]], United States\n| Kenneth Lee Jackson, 19\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 16-year-old Cody Cobbins was shot and killed on a school bus by the older brother of a 17-year-old boy he was arguing with over a seat. The shooter was later sentenced to 40 years in prison on March 5, 1987.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1345&dat=19861009&id=b7ISAAAAIBAJ&sjid=y_kDAAAAIBAJ&pg=7124,2135083 |title=Boy fatally shot while on school bus |publisher=News.google.com |date=1986-10-09 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=DM&p_theme=dm&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0ED3CF204EBF9EFF&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM |title=Man sentenced to 40 years in shooting on S. OAK Cliff school bus |publisher=Nl.newsbank.com |date=1987-03-06 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 4, 1986\n| [[Lewistown, Montana]], United States\n| Kristopher Hans, 14\n| 1 dead\n| 3 injured\n| 14-year-old Kristofer Hans - angry over a failing grade - shot and killed a substitute teacher, later wounding a vice principal and two students. He is now serving two life sentences.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.knowgangs.com/school_resources/timeline/1980_1989/3.php |title=School Shooting Timeline |publisher=Knowgangs.com |date=1986-12-04 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100828163704/http://www.knowgangs.com/school_resources/timeline/1980_1989/3.php |archivedate=2010-08-28 }}</ref>\n|-\n| March 2, 1987\n| [[De Kalb, Missouri]], United States\n| Nathan Ferris, 12\n| 2 dead\n|\n| After constant teasing about his weight, honors student Nathan Ferris used a pistol to kill a student who bullied him in class. Ferris then killed himself with the gun.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crimelibrary.com/serial_killers/weird/kids1/index_1.html |title=School Killers |publisher=Crimelibrary.com |accessdate=2011-03-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140310051132/http://www.crimelibrary.com/serial_killers/weird/kids1/index_1.html |archivedate=2014-03-10 }}</ref>\n|-\n| April 16, 1987\n| [[Detroit]], [[Michigan]], United States\n| Student, 9th Grade\n| 1 dead\n| 3 injured\n| A ninth-grade [[Murray\u2013Wright High School]] student killed Chester Jackson, 17, and wounded Damon Matthews, 17, and Tomeka Turner, 18. This attack was targeted at those students. <ref name=Risen>Risen, James. \"[https://articles.latimes.com/1987-04-17/news/mn-615_1_high-school Athlete Killed in Detroit School Violence]\". ''[[Los Angeles Times]]''. April 17, 1987. Retrieved on November 2, 2012.</ref><ref name=studentkilled>\"[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=KrwsAAAAIBAJ&sjid=-hMEAAAAIBAJ&pg=4645,276164&dq=murray-wright-high-school&hl=en Students shot at high school]\". ''[[Wilmington Morning Star]]''. Friday April 17, 1987. 2A. Retrieved from [[Google Books]] (2 of 31) on November 2, 2012.</ref>\n|-\n| September 28, 1987\n| [[Lansing, Illinois]], United States\n| Blake Docter, 16\n| \n| 1 injured\n| After being kicked off the soccer team for smoking on school grounds, [[Illiana Christian High School]] student Blake Docter, 16, shot and wounded John Hoogewerf, the teacher who had caught him smoking.<ref>{{cite news |newspaper=[[Chicago Tribune]]|first1=Rob |last1=Karwath |url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1987-09-30/news/8703130825_1_second-floor-classroom-shooting-smoking-on-school-grounds|title=Youth Freed On Bond In Shooting Of Teacher |date=September 30, 1987 |accessdate=February 22, 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 6, 1988\n| [[Higham Ferrers, Northamptonshire]], United Kingdom\n| Darren Lloyd Fowler, 16\n| \n| 4 injured\n| Three months after he was expelled, Darren Lloyd Fletcher returned to his former school, Higham Ferrers School, shooting a deputy head in the head, and injuring a teacher and two 12-year old pupils with glass and shrapnel, before he was overpowered by staff. He was out to kill his rival for the affections of a 16-year-old girl who was a student at the school.<ref>{{cite news |newspaper= The Glasgow Herald | title = Boy Rambo gets life | url = https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2507&dat=19880625&id=8jNAAAAAIBAJ&sjid=T1kMAAAAIBAJ&pg=3452,6976776&hl=en | date = June 25, 1988 | accessdate = December 29, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 11, 1988\n| [[Pinellas Park, Florida]], United States\n| Jason Edward Harless, 15 <br> Jason McCoy, 15\n| 1 dead\n| 3 injured\n| [[Pinellas Park High School#School shooting|Pinellas Park High School shooting]]. Jason Harless and Jason McCoy, both students, brought stolen guns to school, where they killed principal Richard Allen , and injured an assistant principal and an assistant physical education teacher. Harless was shot and wounded by police, and McCoy was arrested without injury. Both served prison terms.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=pMUMAAAAIBAJ&sjid=J2EDAAAAIBAJ&pg=6178,5476026&dq= Student was treated at mental hospital], ''[[St. Petersburg Times]]'' (February 13, 1988)</ref>\n|-\n| November 22, 1988\n| [[Abilene, Texas]], United States\n| Mason Staggs, 16\n| \n| 1 injured\n| Mason Staggs, 16, shot Cooper High School teacher Rick Maloney in the face with a derringer, severely injuring him. Staggs then left the school and went fishing.<ref>{{cite news |newspaper=[[Abilene Reporter-News]] |url=http://www.texnews.com/local97/staggs021497.html |title=Mason Staggs denied double jeopardy claim |date=February 14, 1997 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050320190338/http://www.texnews.com/local97/staggs021497.html |archivedate=March 20, 2005 }}</ref>\n|-\n| December 16, 1988\n| [[Virginia Beach, Virginia]], United States\n| Nicholas Elliott, 16\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| Nicholas Elliott came to Atlantic Shores Christian School with a firearm bought by an adult relative. He shot two teachers, one fatally, before entering a portable classroom full of students. The gun jammed and Elliott was tackled. Questioned after the shooting, Elliott complained of being teased and bullied. He was later sentenced to life in prison in 1989.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lorrainewakeland.com/pdfarchive/jammed_gun.pdf |title=Jammed gun holds toll to 1 dead; student held |format=PDF |accessdate=2011-03-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713232358/http://www.lorrainewakeland.com/pdfarchive/jammed_gun.pdf |archive-date=2011-07-13 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5oabRaJVmysC&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_summary_r&cad=0 |title=Leonard Beeghley Homicide:A Sociological Explanation |publisher=Books.google.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 24, 1989\n| [[Rauma, Finland|Rauma]], Finland\n| Tero Toivola, 14\n| 2 dead\n|\n| [[Raumanmeri school shooting]]. Two students, 15-year-old Kristian Johtela and 14-year-old Juha Suominen, were fatally shot by 14-year-old student Tero Toivola at the Raumanmeri [[Secondary School]], in [[Rauma, Finland]]. The shooter claimed to be a victim of bullying.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.yle.fi/news/left/id74423.html|title=School Shootings Rare in Finland|publisher=[[YLE]]|date=2007-11-07|accessdate=2007-11-07}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n===1990s===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:65px;\"| Date\n! style=\"width:85px;\"| Location\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Attacker(s)\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" style=\"width:75px;\"| Dead{{r|group=lower-alpha|note_a}}\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" style=\"width:75px;\"| Injured{{r|group=lower-alpha|note_a}}\n! Description\n|-\n| May 20, 1990\n| [[Centerville, Tennessee]], United States\n| Donald Wayne Givens, 50\n| 1 dead\n| \n| Hickman County High School Principal Ron Wallace, 41, was shot and killed by Science teacher Donald Wayne Givens, 50, when Givens was caught by Wallace attempting to set fire to several areas of the high school two days before graduation ceremonies were scheduled.<ref>{{cite news|title=School hit by slaying and blaze Principal shot; teacher held|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1310&dat=19900521&id=wcJWAAAAIBAJ&sjid=0eoDAAAAIBAJ&pg=6655,5338612|newspaper=The Register-Guard|date=May 21, 1990}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 21, 1990\n| [[Houston, Texas]], United States\n| ..., 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| A 16-year-old girl fatally stabbed her classmate, 18-year-old Anthony Johnson, in the upper back with a [[hunting knife]] in a classroom at [[Jesse H. Jones High School]], in [[Houston]], [[Texas]]; Johnson later died at [[Ben Taub Hospital]]. The suspect was then placed in the Harris County Juvenile Probation Department. It was reported that the possible motive was the victim making an insulting comment about the suspect's clothing.<ref>Markley, Melanie. \"[https://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl?id=1996_1371129 Studying our Schools: Challenges / Safety matters: Issue is No. 1 concern with parents].\" ''[[Houston Chronicle]]''. October 13, 1996.</ref><ref>Hanson, Eric. \"[https://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl?id=1990_731137 Teen fatally stabbed in classroom / Victim pays for insult to girl's shorts with life].\" ''[[Houston Chronicle]]''. September 22, 1990.</ref>\n|-\n| April 10, 1991\n| [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]], United Kingdom\n| Barbara Glover, 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 16-year-old Diane Watson is stabbed to death by 16-year-old Barbara Glover at Whitehill Secondary School in the Dennistoun area of Glasgow.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/616759.stm|work=BBC News|title=Parents protest at killer's parole bid|date=January 24, 2000|accessdate=May 8, 2010}}</ref> Both Watson and Glover were students at the school.<ref>{{cite web|author=The Committee Office, House of Commons |url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200203/cmselect/cmcumeds/458/458w125.htm |title=Appendix 124 Memorandum submitted by Margaret and James Watson |publisher=Publications.parliament.uk |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| April 23, 1991\n| [[Compton, California]], United States\n|\n| 1 dead\n|\n| A teenager aimed and fired a handgun at a security guard who had chased him and three friends off the grounds of Ralph J. Bunche Middle School. However, instead of hitting his intended target, the bullet struck 11-year-old bystander Alejandro Vargas, a student at the school, killing him.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://articles.latimes.com/1991-04-24/local/me-536_1_security-guard |title=Shot Fired at Guard Kills Boy at School |publisher=Articles.latimes.com |date=1991-09-19 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |first1=Ron |last1=Russell |first2=Michele |last2=Fuetsch}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 9, 1991\n| [[Reserve, Louisiana]], United States\n| Brenda Carter, 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 19-year-old senior Debbie Morantes is stabbed to death by 16-year-old sophomore Brenda Carter inside the cafeteria of East St. John High School. Brenda Carter was convicted of second-degree murder two years later.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=AD&p_theme=ad&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB4765F795DECFF&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM |title=LaPlace girl booked with murder of schoolmate |publisher=Nl.newsbank.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=AD&p_theme=ad&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB477531F5A8C2D&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM |title=Teen's sentencing set for next month |publisher=Nl.newsbank.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| June 19, 1991\n| [[Coffs Harbour]], Australia\n| ...,13\n| \n| 3 injured \n| A student brought a rifle to [[Orara High School]], injuring 2 teachers and 1 student. The shooter was tackled to the ground by fellow students.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.apnewsarchive.com/1991/Student-Shoots-Three-Outside-His-School/id-9a37235e1f46bbf7d2e0acc5415db1b8|title=Student Shoots Three Outside His School|website=www.apnewsarchive.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 30, 1991\n| [[Indianapolis, Indiana]], United States\n| Edward C. Ector, 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 17-year-old Bertram Bowman is stabbed to death in the cafeteria of [[Arlington High School, (Indianapolis)|Arlington High School]], reportedly in a dispute over a girl. Police arrested 15-year-old Edward C. Ector after the attack.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=aA0gAAAAIBAJ&sjid=o2UFAAAAIBAJ&pg=1533,76036&dq=school+stabbing&hl=en |title=Teen stabbed to death at school |publisher=News.google.ca |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=1sBJAAAAIBAJ&sjid=ohANAAAAIBAJ&pg=3661,77460&dq=school+stabbing&hl=en |title=Stabbing draws attention to violence in high schools |publisher=News.google.ca |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=1cBJAAAAIBAJ&sjid=ohANAAAAIBAJ&pg=4845,14264&dq=bertram+bowman&hl=en |title=School argument results in killing |publisher=News.google.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 9, 1991\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n|\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 17-year-old Tryon Whittaker was shot to death by another youth outside of James Monroe High School in [[The Bronx]]. The boys had reportedly got into an argument and Whittaker challenged the other youth to a fight. The youth then walked away, but returned with a gun and shot Whittaker.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1991/10/09/nyregion/a-bronx-youth-is-shot-to-death-outside-a-school.html |title=A Bronx Youth Is Shot to Death Outside a School |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1991-10-09 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |first=John T. |last=McQuiston}}</ref>\n|-\n| November 14, 1991\n| [[Houston, Texas]], United States\n| ..., 16\n|\n| 1 injured\n| 18-year-old Francisco Contreras was shot four times in his feet and leg outside the cafeteria of [[Milby High School]], in [[Houston]], [[Texas]], by a 16-year-old student, who was arrested afterward. The attack was targeted.<ref>\"[https://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl?id=1991_822573 Shooting at school fuels calls for more security].\" ''[[Houston Chronicle]]''. November 15, 1991.</ref>\n|-\t\n| November 25, 1991\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| Jason Bentley, 14\n| 1 dead\n|\n| [[Thomas Jefferson High School (Brooklyn)|Thomas Jefferson High School]]. A stray bullet kills a 16-year-old student during an argument between two other teens. Shooter Jason Bentley, 14, is sentenced in 1992 to three to nine years in prison.<ref name=\"PAC\"/>\n|-\t\n| February 26, 1992\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| Kahlil Sumpter, 15\n| 2 dead\n|\n| [[Thomas Jefferson High School (Brooklyn)|Thomas Jefferson High School]] was the scene of its second shooting of the school year, when a 15-year-old shot and killed two other students in a targeted attack. The shooter, Kahlil Sumpter, is sentenced in 1993 to between 6 2/3 and 20 years in prison, and is released in 1998.<ref name=\"PAC\"/>\n|-\n| May 1, 1992\n| [[Olivehurst, California]], United States\n| Eric Houston, 20\n| 4 dead\n| 10 injured\n| [[Lindhurst High School shooting]]. Armed with a pistol, 20-year-old Eric Houston took hostages at his former high school, killing four people and wounding 10. His motive was his inability to find a good job because he had failed a grade at school. He was given the [[death penalty]] for the shooting.\n|-\n| May 14, 1992\n| [[Napa, California]], United States\n| John McMahan, 14\n|\n| 2 injured\n| Armed with a [[.357 Magnum|.357-caliber]] [[pistol]], 14-year-old student John McMahan opened fire in a science classroom, wounding two.<ref name=\"Understanding lethal school violence\">{{cite book|last = Moore|first = Mark H.|author2=Carol V. Petrie |author3=Anthony A. Braga |author4=Brenda L. McLaughlin |title = Deadly Lessons: Understanding Lethal School Violence|publisher= [[National Academies Press]]|year = 2003|location = Washington, D.C.|page = 294|url = http://www.nap.edu/openbook.php?isbn=0309084121}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 11, 1992\n| [[Amarillo, Texas]], United States\n| Randy Earl Matthews, 17; ..., 15\n|\n| 6 injured\n| Six students were shot at [[Palo Duro High School]]. All survived the shooting. Police later arrested 17-year-old Randy Earl Matthews and an unidentified 15-year-old boy in connection with the shooting.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1992/09/12/us/student-wounds-6-at-high-school.html |title=Student Wounds 6 at High School |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1992-09-12 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 21, 1992\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| Michael Bubb, 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Damion Ennis, 15, is stabbed to death by a fellow student in a hallway of South Shore High School.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1992/09/22/nyregion/boy-15-is-fatally-stabbed-at-school-in-brooklyn.html |title=Boy, 15, Is Fatally Stabbed at School in Brooklyn |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1992-09-22 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |first=Robert D. |last=McFadden}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 18, 1993\n| [[Grayson, Kentucky]], United States\n| Scott Pennington, 17\n| 2 dead\n|\n| Scott Pennington shot and killed teacher Deanna McDavid and custodian Marvin Hicks after entering McDavid's classroom at East Carter High School. Pennington was later found guilty of the murders and sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>[http://www2.indystar.com/library/factfiles/crime/school_violence/school_shootings.html School Shootings] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110717151825/http://www2.indystar.com/library/factfiles/crime/school_violence/school_shootings.html |date=2011-07-17 }}. .indystar.com. Retrieved on 2010-08-16.</ref>\n|-\n| February 1, 1993\n| [[Amityville, New York]], United States\n| Shem S. McCoy, 17\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| Shem S. McCoy, 17, shot two people, both cousins of his, at Amityville High School. One of those shot, Randel Artis, would die of his gunshot injuries. The three boys had apparently been engaged in a long running dispute.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1993/02/03/nyregion/youth-arraigned-in-killing-at-amityville-high-school.html |title=Youth Arraigned in Killing At Amityville High School |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1993-02-03 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |first=John T. |last=McQuiston}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 22, 1993\n| [[Los Angeles, California]], United States\n| Robert Heard, 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 15-year-old Robert Heard shot and killed 17-year-old Michael Shean Ensley in a corridor of [[Reseda High School]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://articles.latimes.com/1993-06-05/local/me-43640_1_reseda-high-school |title=Fatal Shooting at School Prompts Project to Spread Anti-Weapons Message \u2013 Los Angeles Times |publisher=Articles.latimes.com |date=1993-06-05 |accessdate=2009-07-03|first=Tracey|last=Kaplan}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 24, 1993\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| Justin Rodriguez, 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 15-year-old Angel Jimenez is stabbed to death by another 15-year-old student in a hallway of Junior High School 25. The stabbing was sparked by a dispute between the two boys over who owned a pair of sunglasses.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1993/02/25/nyregion/15-year-old-dies-in-attack-in-school-hall.html |title=15-Year-Old Dies in Attack In School Hall |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1993-02-25 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |first=Sam |last=Dillon}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 18, 1993\n| [[Harlem, Georgia]], United States\n| Edward Bryant Gillom, 15\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| Edward Bryant Gillom, a freshman at Harlem High School, shot two fellow students, killing 15-year-old Ronrecas Gibson.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://chat.augustachronicle.com/stories/1999/11/28/met_276184.shtml |title=A look at the 20th century: 1993 |publisher=Chat.augustachronicle.com |date=1999-11-28 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120707130426/http://chat.augustachronicle.com/stories/1999/11/28/met_276184.shtml |archive-date=2012-07-07 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| April 15, 1993\n| [[Acushnet, Massachusetts]], United States\n| David Taber, 44\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 44-year-old David Taber invades Ford Middle School and takes three hostages. He later shoots and kills school nurse Carol Day. He is found not guilty of the murder by reason of insanity.<ref name=\"PAC\"/>\n|-\n| May 24, 1993\n| [[Pennsburg, Pennsylvania]], United States\n| Jason Smith, 15\n| 1 dead\n| \n| [[Upper Perkiomen High School]] student, 15-year-old, Jason Smith shoots and kills another student who had bullied him. He is sentenced to between 12 and 25 years in prison.<ref name=\"PAC\"/><ref>{{cite web | url=http://articles.philly.com/1993-10-15/news/25936622_1_shot-classmate-jason-michael-smith-michael-swann | title=Prison Term For Murder At School Jason Michael Smith Received 12 1/2 To 25 Years For Shooting A Classmate At Upper Perkiomen High School In May. |publisher=philly.com | date=October 15, 1993 | accessdate=December 11, 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 17, 1993\n| [[Sheridan, Wyoming]], United States\n| Kevin Newman, 29\n| 1 dead\n| 4 injured\n| 4 students in a physical education class were wounded at Central Middle School in Sheridan, Wyoming, when 29-year-old Kevin Newman fired at them with a handgun while the class was doing lessons outdoors. He then committed suicide by shooting himself in the head. A suicide note found in Newman's motel room revealed that he was unhappy with his life, and thought of himself as an evil person.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=lm0xAAAAIBAJ&sjid=VwMEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6650,4748310&dq= Gunman attacks school, kills himself], ''[[Toledo Blade]]'' (September 18, 1993)</ref><ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=bR0PAAAAIBAJ&sjid=4oQDAAAAIBAJ&pg=5130,5790941&dq= Suicide note says Wyoming gunman \"evil\"], ''[[The Deseret News]]'' (September 27, 1993)</ref>\n|-\n| September 17, 1993\n| [[Darien, Illinois]], United States\n| Phillip Powell, 15\n| 1 dead\n| \n| 15-year-old Phillip Powell killed 17-year-old Barrett Modisette in Hinsdale South High School\u2019s parking lot. Powell was a self-described gang member, who shot Barrett because Barrett was protecting his younger brother from Powell's verbal bullying. Powell was tried as an adult and was sentenced to 37 years in prison in 1994.<ref>[http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1994-07-27/news/9407270381_1_student-s-death-gang-violence-sentenced 16-year-old Killer Gets 37 Years], \u2018\u2019[[Chicago Tribune]]\u2019\u2019 (July 27, 1994)</ref>\n|-\n| October 6, 1993\n| [[Hausleiten]], Austria\n| ..., 13\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| A 13-year-old student, waiting at the entrance of the [[Hauptschule]] in Hausleiten, shot and wounded the principal of the school with a rifle before committing suicide. The student was caught smoking the day before and the principal told the boy he had to inform his parents about it.<ref>[http://diepresse.com/home/panorama/oesterreich/310346/index.do?direct=310340&_vl_backlink=/home/panorama/index.do&selChannel= Gewehr, Revolver, Messer im Klassenzimmer], ''[[Die Presse]]'' (June 13, 2007)</ref>\n|-\n| December 1, 1993\n| [[Wauwatosa, Wisconsin]], United States\n| Leonard McDowell, 21\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Leonard McDowell, a 21-year-old former student at [[Wauwatosa West High School]], shot Associate Principal Dale Breitlow three times with a .44-cal. Taurus revolver in a second-floor hallway. McDowell was found guilty of the murder and sane at the time of the shooting. His life sentence was upheld by the state Court of Appeals in April, 1997.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.jsonline.com/story/index.aspx?id=506749|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071014115039/http://www.jsonline.com/story/index.aspx?id=506749|url-status=dead|title=Milwaukee - home|archivedate=October 14, 2007}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 17, 1993\n| [[Chelsea, Michigan]], United States\n| Stephen Leith\n| 1 dead\n| 2 injured\n| Steve Leith, a science teacher at [[Chelsea High School (Michigan)|Chelsea High School]], walked into a staff meeting being held at the school and shot and killed the district superintendent, and also wounded the school principal and a teacher. Leith was then arrested by police.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1993/12/17/us/police-arrest-a-teacher-in-school-shootings.html |title=Police Arrest a Teacher in School Shootings |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1993-12-17 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=pOsVAAAAIBAJ&sjid=5hQEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6924,418870&dq=chelsea+michigan+school&hl=en |title=Teacher arrested in school shootings |publisher=News.google.ca |date=1993-12-17 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 31, 1994\n| [[Seattle, Washington]], United States\n| Darrell Cloud, 24\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 24-year-old Darrell Cloud entered Whitman Middle School and shot his former teacher, 45-year-old Neal Summers, to death. Cloud would serve nine years in prison for the murder. The motive for the shooting was sexual abuse that was alleged to have been perpetrated by Summers against Cloud since Cloud was 13 years old.<ref>{{cite news|last=Shaw |first=Linda |url=http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/localnews/2002162113_cloud26m.html |title=Abuse victim who killed teacher settles with district |publisher=Seattletimes.nwsource.com |date=2005-01-27 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 1, 1994\n| [[Simi Valley, California]], United States\n| Chad Patrick Hubbard, 14\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 14-year old Phillip Hernandez killed his bully, also 14-year-old Chad Patrick Hubbard, by stabbing him in the heart with a pocket knife.<ref>http://www.columbine-angels.com/School_Violence_1993-1994.htm</ref><ref>https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1994-07-30-me-21582-story.html</ref><ref>https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1994-07-30-me-21582-story.html</ref>\n|-\n| March 1, 1994\n| [[Boonville, Missouri]], United States\n| Dante D. Hayes, 33\n| 2 dead\n| \n| Dante D. Hayes, 33, a hunter and ex-convict, shot and killed Richard Vancena, 58, a cafeteria manager, and Robin Michelle Coleman, 33, a cook, in the mess hall of [[Kemper Military School]]. He was drunk and looking for his wife Anna Hayes with whom he had a fight the night before. No students were harmed.<ref>{{cite news|author=Associated Press |url=http://www.deseretnews.com/article/339317/GUNMAN-KILLS-2-AT-MISSOURI-MILITARY-SCHOOL.html?pg=all |title=GUNMAN KILLS 2 AT MISSOURI MILITARY SCHOOL |newspaper=Deseret News |date=1994-03-02 |accessdate=2014-06-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 25, 1994\n| [[Cherokee County, Georgia]], United States\n| Brian Head, 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 15-year-old Brian Head shot and killed himself during his economics class at [[Etowah High School (Georgia)|Etowah High School]]. Head had been a longtime target for bullies because of his weight and thick glasses. His father, Bill, subsequently successfully lobbied for a law that criminalized bullying and required schools to alert parents of bullied children.\n|-\n| March 28, 1994\n| [[Acklam, Middlesbrough]], United Kingdom\n| Stephen Wilkinson, 29\n| 1 dead\n| 2 injured\n| Stephen Wilkinson burst into a mathematics classroom at [[Hall Garth Community Arts College]] and stabbed three children, including 12-year-old Nikki Conroy, who later died from her injuries.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/talks-to-comfort-pupils-after-killing-counselling-starts-for-children-still-in-shock-after-classroom-stabbing-malcolm-pithers-reports-1432491.html |title=Talks to comfort pupils after killing: Counselling starts for children still in shock after classroom stabbing |publisher=Independent.co.uk |date=1994-03-30 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |location=London |first=Malcolm |last=Pithers}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 26, 1994\n| [[Union, Kentucky]], United States\n| [[Clay Shrout]], 17\n| 4 dead\n|\n| Clay Shrout kills his mother, father, and two younger sisters before embarking a [[hostage situation]] in a [[trigonometry]] classroom. He's now serving life in prison.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.enquirer.com/editions/2004/05/25/loc_shrout25prison.html |title=Clay Shrout reported of prison behavioral problems |publisher=Enquirer.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| June 17, 1994\n| [[Holywood, Northern Ireland]], United Kingdom\n| [[Sullivan Upper School#The 1994 attack|Garnet Bell]], 46\n|\n| 6 injured\n| A former pupil bearing a grudge entered an assembly hall at [[Sullivan Upper School]], and used a [[flamethrower]] to attack students taking [[Advanced Level (UK)|A-Level]] examinations. Six were injured; three seriously. Bell was later sentenced to life behind prison, but died there in the hospital wing on March 26, 1997 from cancer.\n|-\n| September 19, 1994\n| [[Soweto]], South Africa\n| ..., 18\n|\n| 7 injured\n| An 18-year-old student shot and wounded seven of his schoolmates with a rifle, after he had been reprimanded. The youth then escaped in his father's car.<ref>Amok wegen R\u00fcge, ''[[Blick]]'' (September 20, 1994)</ref>\n|-\n| October 12, 1994\n| [[Greensboro, North Carolina]], United States\n| Nicholas Atkinson, 16\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| Nicholas Atkinson, a 16-year-old [[Grimsley High School]] student, returned to campus after being suspended. He proceeded to shoot and wound the assistant principal with a 9&nbsp;mm handgun, before committing suicide.\n|-\n| October 25, 1994\n| [[Mount Vernon, New York]], United States\n| Hopeton Minott, 17\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 17-year-old Shebule Jackson is stabbed to death by fellow student Hopeton Minott in a corridor of Mount Vernon High School.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1994/10/25/nyregion/student-slain-at-school-in-mt-vernon.html |title=Student Slain At School In Mt. Vernon |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1994-10-25 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |first=Jacques |last=Steinberg}}</ref>\n|-\n| November 7, 1994\n| [[Wickliffe,