ewsweek.com/id/147790&GT1=43002 |work=[[Newsweek]] |date=2008-07-19 |accessdate=2008-07-23 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080722131056/http://www.newsweek.com/id/147790%26GT1%3D43002 |archivedate=July 22, 2008 |url-status=dead }}</ref> McInerney was sentenced to 21 years of prison on the charge of second-degree murder. \n|-\n| February 25, 2008\n| [[Leizhou]],<br>[[Guangdong]],<br>[[China]]\n| Chen Wenzhen\n| 3 dead\n| 4 injured\n| Chen Wenzhen, a [[Dropping out|school drop-out]] with mental illness, attacked six students with a knife at Leizhou No. 2 Middle School, in [[Leizhou]], [[China]], killing two of them. He then committed suicide by stabbing himself in the abdomen and jumping out of a window in the fifth floor.<ref name=\"xinhaunet226\">{{cite web |title = 3 dead, 4 injured in school killing in S. China |author= Liang, Yan |publisher= [[Xinhuanet]]|date = February 26, 2008| url =http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2008-02/26/content_7669100.htm|accessdate = 2009-05-07}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 6, 2008\n| [[Kiryat Moshe]], [[Jerusalem]], [[Israel]]\n| Alaa Abu Dhein, 26\n| 9 dead\n| 11 injured\n| [[Mercaz HaRav massacre]]. A lone Palestinian gunman shot multiple students at the Mercaz HaRav yeshiva, a religious school in Jerusalem, Israel, after which the gunman himself was shot dead. Eight students and the perpetrator were killed. Eleven more were wounded, five of them placed in serious to critical condition. The attack began at 8:30 p.m. local time and ended sixteen minutes later. The attacker was stopped by long-time Mercaz HaRav student Yitzhak Dadon and off-duty Israel Defense Forces Captain David Shapira, who killed him with their personal firearms. <ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.reuters.com/article/2008/03/07/idUSL07359144 |title= Gunman kills 8 in Jerusalem Jewish college |publisher=Reuters.com |date=2008-03-07 |website= Reuter\u2019s}}</ref>\n|-\n| April 16, 2008\n| [[Fresno, California]], United States\n| Jesus Carrizales, 17\n| 1 dead\n| 1 