hool.stabbing/index.html |title=Student killed in fight at Florida school, officials say |publisher=Cnn.com |date=2009-09-15 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5i8kU66PQjcHD1SSb0eoMcYCyv2xgD9AP4VUO0|title=Mom defends Fla. teen charged in school stabbing|accessdate=10 January 2020}}</ref> In November 2011, Rodriguez was sentenced to 40 years and 10 years of probation.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://miami.cbslocal.com/2011/11/29/former-gables-student-to-be-sentenced-for-stabbing-classmate-2/ |title=Former Gables Student Sentenced For Stabbing Classmate|date=November 29, 2011}}</ref> \n|-\n| September 16, 2009\n| [[Antioch, California|Antioch]],<br>[[California]],<br>United States\n| Yousuf Mohammad Aziz, 19\n|\n| 1 injured\n| A 16-year-old student of [[Deer Valley High School (Antioch, California)|Deer Valley High School]], in [[Antioch, California]], was shot in the arm and torso after an argument between two groups of young men. The shots were fired from a vehicle, which then drove off.<ref name=\"sfgate917\">{{cite news|first=Kevin| last=Fagan| title=Loud music leads to teen's shooting in Antioch|date=2009-09-17|work=San Francisco Chronicle|url = http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2009/09/16/BA4B19O1ER.DTL|accessdate = 2009-09-17}}</ref> The victim was [[air ambulance|lifted by air]] to [[John Muir Medical Center]] in [[Walnut Creek, California|Walnut Creek]] and underwent surgery. Yousuf Mohammad Aziz, a 19-year-old graduate of Deer Valley, was arrested on September 18 in connection with the shooting.<ref name=\"contracosta919\">{{cite news|first=Hilary| last=Costa| title=\nAntioch school officials stand by emergency protocol|date=2009-09-19|publisher= [[Contra Costa Times]]|url =\nhttp://www.contracostatimes.com/education/ci_13377161|accessdate = 2009-09-19}}</ref> Aziz was found guilty of attempted murder, and was sentenced to 7 years to life in prison. \n|-\n| September 17, 2009\n| [[Ansbach]],<br>[[Bavaria]],<br>Germany\n| Georg R., 18\n|\n| 11 injured\n| [[Ansbach school attack]]. An 18-year-old student identified as Georg R. arrived at Carolinum High School in [[Ansbach]], Germany armed with an [[axe]], knives and [[Molotov cocktails]]. He injured nine students and a teacher at the school before he himself was shot by police. Two of the injured students as well as the attacker were reported to be in critical condition.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/teenage-attacker-wounds-school-students-germany/story?id=8599482 |title=Teenage Attacker Wounds 9 School Students in Germany |publisher=Abcnews.go.com |date=2009-09-17 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 23, 2009\n| [[Tyler, Texas|Tyler]],<br>[[Texas]],<br>United States\n|\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 50-year-old Todd Henry, a [[special education]] teacher at [[John Tyler High School]], was fatally stabbed by a student inside a classroom at the school. Henry later died of his injuries at a local hospital. The attacker was taken into custody.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abcnews.go.com/US/texas-teacher-stabbed-death-student-classroom/story?id=8653789 |title=Texas Teacher Stabbed to Death by Student in Classroom |publisher=Abcnews.go.com |date=2009-09-23 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 16, 2009\n| [[Carolina Forest, South Carolina|Carolina Forest]],<br>[[South Carolina]],<br>United States\n| Trevor Varinecz, 16\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| Trevor Varinecz, a junior at [[Carolina Forest High School]], attacked and stabbed police officer Marcus Rhodes, the School Resource Officer, inside his office. Rhodes then shot Varinecz in self defense. Varinecz later died in hospital.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www2.scnow.com/scp/news/local/grand_strand/article/carolina_forest_high_school_on_lockdown/81325/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091019124426/http://www2.scnow.com/scp/news/local/grand_strand/article/carolina_forest_high_school_on_lockdown/81325 |url-status=de