etteville, North Carolina]], United States\n| Charles Underwood, 15\n|\n| 1 injured\n| A 15-year-old girl was shot in the neck at [[Cape Fear High School]]. She was hospitalized for two months at [[Duke University Hospital]] in serious condition. A [[.22]]-caliber rifle was used in the attack. A student of the school, 15-year-old Charles Underwood, was arrested and charged with attempted murder.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/10/24/cape-fear-high-school-sho_n_1028933.html?icid=maing-grid7%7Cmain5%7Cdl2%7Csec1_lnk2%7C106948 |work=Huffington Post | title=Cape Fear High School Shooting: 1 Student Shot, Wounded At North Carolina School | date=24 October 2011}}</ref> Underwood was convicted of attempted first-degree murder and was sentenced to 15 years in prison.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.wral.com/teen-moves-forward-after-cape-fear-high-shooting/12317579/ |work=[[WRAL-TV|WRAL]] | title=Teen moves forward after Cape Fear High shooting | date=April 8, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 24, 2011\n| [[Everett, Washington]], United States\n| Female student, 15\n|\n| 2 injured\n| A 15-year-old student stabbed two female students with a butcher knife at [[Snohomish High School]]. One of the victims was stabbed 20 times, mainly in the heart and lungs, and was critically injured. The victims were both chosen at random, and the victims and suspect did not know each other. The attacker was convicted of attempted murder and was sentenced to 13 years in prison.<ref>Chamberlain, Lindsey. [http://www.king5.com/news/local/Snohomish-girl-15-held-in-high-school-stabbing-132543838.html Snohomish teen suspect said she didn't know girls stabbed in attack] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111231045458/http://www.king5.com/news/local/Snohomish-girl-15-held-in-high-school-stabbing-132543838.html |date=2011-12-31 }}, ''[[King5]]'' (October 26, 2011)</ref><ref>[http://www.kirotv.com/news/news/crime-law/teen-girl-maniacal-knife-attack-may-be-tried-adult/nLM3C