ugiah-Victim in high school murder was 'going for lunch |date=2007-09-13 |publisher=[[CBC News]] |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/victim-in-high-school-murder-was-going-for-lunch-1.668220 |accessdate=2009-06-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090724115200/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/victim-in-high-school-murder-was-going-for-lunch-1.668220 |archivedate=July 24, 2009 }}</ref> No suspects were ever sought in the stabbing.\n|-\n| September 28, 2007\n| [[Oroville, California|Oroville]],<br>[[California]],<br>United States\n| Greg Dean Wright, 17\n|\n| \n| 17-year-old student Greg Wright [[n:Hostage situation at California high school ends peacefully|held twenty-seven students and a teacher hostage]] in a classroom at [[Oroville, California#Oroville Union High School District|Las Plumas High School]], in [[Oroville, California]], for about two hours before surrendering to law enforcement;<ref name=\"pressdemooroville928\">{{cite news|first=Juliet|last=Williams|title=Oroville shooting ends quietly|date=2007-09-28|url=http://www1.pressdemocrat.com/article/20070929/NEWS/709290404|work=[[Press Democrat]]|accessdate=2009-04-21|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090706034717/http://www1.pressdemocrat.com/article/20070929/NEWS/709290404|archivedate=2009-07-06}}</ref> all but three of the hostages were released an hour within. Several shots were fired towards the air from Wright's weapon, a [[.22 Long Rifle|.22-caliber]] [[semi-automatic handgun]], during the crisis.<ref name=\"sacbee928\">{{cite news|first=Niesha|last=Lofing |author2=Ryan Lillis |author3=Dorothy Korber |title=Hostage situation ends at California high school.|date=2007-09-28|url =http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-33008402_ITM|work=[[The Sacramento Bee]]|accessdate = 2009-04-21}}</ref><ref name=\"cbs13929\">{{cite news|title=Arrest Made After Hostages Held At Oroville School|date=2007-09-29|publisher=[[KOVR|CBS 13]]|url =http:/