, South Carolina|Carolina Forest]],<br>[[South Carolina]],<br>United States\n| Trevor Varinecz, 16\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| Trevor Varinecz, a junior at [[Carolina Forest High School]], attacked and stabbed police officer Marcus Rhodes, the School Resource Officer, inside his office. Rhodes then shot Varinecz in self defense. Varinecz later died in hospital.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www2.scnow.com/scp/news/local/grand_strand/article/carolina_forest_high_school_on_lockdown/81325/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091019124426/http://www2.scnow.com/scp/news/local/grand_strand/article/carolina_forest_high_school_on_lockdown/81325 |url-status=dead |archive-date=2009-10-19 |title=Carolina Forest student shot, killed; resource officer stabbed |publisher=.scnow.com |accessdate=2011-03-12 }}</ref>\n|-\n| October 30, 2009\n| [[Long Beach, California|Long Beach]],<br>[[California]],<br>United States\n| Tom Vinson, 16;<br>Daivion Davis, 16\n| 1 dead\n| 2 injured\n| 16-year-old Melody Ross, a junior at [[Wilson Classical High School]], was fatally shot leaving a [[homecoming]] game at the school. Two males, aged 18 and 20, were also injured in the shooting. Tom Vinson and Daivion Davis were later arrested and charged with murder and two counts of attempted murder.<ref>{{cite news|last=Vives |first=Ruben |url=https://www.latimes.com/news/local/la-me-wilson-shooting1-2009nov01,0,3566754.story |title=Student at Long Beach's Wilson High fatally shot after homecoming game |publisher=Latimes.com |date=2009-11-01 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Decker |first=Cathleen |url=https://www.latimes.com/news/local/la-me-week8-2009nov08,0,7914780.story |title=Melody Ross touches the world |publisher=Latimes.com |date=2009-11-08 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/homicidereport/2009/11/times-coverage-funeral-held-for-melody-ross-16.html |title=Funeral held for Melody Ross, 16 |work=LA Times |date=2009-11-15 |accessd