84039/story.html|title=Teacher stabbed to death over 'bad marks'|accessdate=10 January 2020}}</ref> Eight months later he was convicted of murder and sentenced to 14 years in prison and placement in a psychiatric facility.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spiegel.de/panorama/justiz/0,1518,724262,00.html |title=Gericht verurteilt Ex-Sch\u00fcler zu 14 Jahren Haft |publisher=Spiegel.de |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 23, 2010\n| [[Littleton, Colorado|Littleton]],<br>[[Colorado]],<br>United States\n| Bruco Strong Eagle Eastwood, 32\n|\n| 2 injured\n| A 32-year-old gunman, identified as Bruco Strong Eagle Eastwood, armed with a [[.30-06]] [[Winchester Model 70]] [[bolt-action rifle]], opened fire on students at [[Deer Creek Middle School]] at 3:30 pm (MST) as school was being let out in [[Littleton, Colorado]]. The gunman was later tackled by a math teacher and the teacher turned him into the police when they arrived on scene. The gunman shot and injured two students at the school before he was taken into custody. Eastwood was placed into a mental health facility for life.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/two-teens-injured-in-colorado-school-shooting/article1479363/ |title=Two teens injured in Colorado school shooting |publisher=Theglobeandmail.com |accessdate=2011-03-12 |location=Toronto |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100227030853/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/two-teens-injured-in-colorado-school-shooting/article1479363/ |archivedate=February 27, 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2010/CRIME/02/24/colorado.school.shooting/?hpt=T2 |title=School shooting suspect identified |publisher=Cnn.com |date=2010-02-24 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 17, 2010\n| [[Deerfield Beach]],<br>[[Florida]]<br>United States\n| Wayne Treacy, 15\n|\n| 1 injured\n| 15-year-old Wayne Treacy stomped and kicked 15-year-old Josie Lou Ratley's head repeatedly with steel-toed boots. The attack occurred at a bus stop on the grounds of Deerfield Beach Middle School, shortly after school was let out. Ratley was critically injured and was in a [[coma]] for several weeks, and underwent major surgery to repair a portion of her skull. In 2012, Treacy was found guilty of attempted first-degree murder and was sentenced to 20 years of prison and 10 years of probation.<ref>{{cite news|author=Anderson, Curt|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/10/22/wayne-treacy-sentenced-josie-lou-ratley-beating_n_2000504.html|title=Wayne Treacy Sentenced In Josie Lou Ratley School Stomping Case (VIDEO)|work=[[The Huffington Post]] |date=October 22, 2012 |accessdate=July 16, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Chang, Daniel|url=http://www.miamiherald.com/2012/07/10/2890170/surgeon-in-treacy-trial-ratley.html|title=Surgeon in Treacy trial: \u2018Ratley lucky to be alive\u2019 |newspaper=[[Miami Herald]] |date=July 10, 2012 |accessdate=July 16, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Anderson, Curt|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/07/16/wayne-treacy-guilty-convicted-verdict-josie-lou-ratley_n_1677103.html|title=Wayne Treacy Guilty In Beating Of Josie Lou Ratley At Deerfield Beach Middle School (VIDEO)|work=[[The Huffington Post]] |date=July 16, 2012 |accessdate=July 16, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 30, 2010\n| [[Oshawa]],<br>[[Ontario]]<br>Canada\n| Jacques Amakon, 18\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Michael McDonald, a 16-year-old student at [[Monsignor Paul Dwyer Catholic High School]], was stabbed to death at a bus stop across from the school. Jacques Amakon, an 18-year-old student, was arrested after the stabbing and charged with [[second-degree murder]]. It was reported that the two students were involved in a dispute.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/article/787988--teens-watch-as-schoolmate-stabbed-to-death-in-oshawa |title=Teens watch as schoolmate stabbed to death in Oshawa |publisher=Thestar.com |date= March 31, 2010|accessdate=2011-03-12 |location=Toronto |first1=