are, 17\n|\n| 2 injured\n| Two students were shot and wounded in front of [[Mumford High School]]. A 17-year-old, Steven Jamal Hare, was tried as an adult and charged with assault with intent to kill. In 2012, Hare was sentenced to 27 years of prison.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://statecasefiles.justia.com/documents/michigan/court-of-appeals-unpublished/305104.pdf?ts=1348661231 |title=PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF MICHIGAN VS. STEVEN JAMAL HARE |publisher=State of Michigan |accessdate=September 5, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 10, 2010\n| [[Santa Clarita, California|Santa Clarita]],<br>[[California]],<br>United States\n| Female student\n|\n| 2 injured\n| A 16-year-old girl at [[William S. Hart High School]] was stabbed on campus with a kitchen knife, during a lunchtime fight over a boy with another female student. The victim was taken to [[Henry Mayo Newhall Memorial Hospital]] with a stab wound to the chest. The girl believed to have done the stabbing was also hospitalized with unspecified injuries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/lanow/2010/10/16-year-old-hart-high-student-stabbed-during-lunchtime-fight-on-newhall-campus.html |title=High school student in Newhall stabbed in fight believed to be over boy |publisher=Latimes.com |accessdate=2015-09-11}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 24, 2010\n| [[Topeka, Kansas|Topeka]],<br>[[Kansas]],<br>United States\n| Coty R. Newman, 21,<br>Austin C. Tabor, 19,<br>Samantha L. Hochard, 20\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| 20-year-old Matthew C. Mitchell was shot to death on the grounds of Topeka West High School. An unidentified juvenile was also injured in the shooting but was expected to recover. Police arrested three suspects.<ref>{{cite web|author=staff writers |url=http://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/breaking-news/one-person-killed-one-injured-in-shooting-at-kansas-high-school/story-e6frf7jx-1225943178603 |title=One person killed, one injured in shooting at Kansas high school |publisher=Heraldsun.com.au |date=2010-10-25 |accessdate=2011-03