taneously shot at him.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.southernmarylandchronicle.com/2018/03/26/smcso-releases-timeline-of-great-mills-high-school-shooting/|title=SMCSO releases timeline of Great Mills High School shooting |date=March 26, 2018 |work=TheSouthernMarylanChronicle}}</ref> \n|-\n|{{Dts|March 21, 2018}}\n|[[Shadrinsk]], Russia\n| Student, 13\n|\n| 7 injured\n| A 13-year-old girl opened fire with a gas pistol at her school in Russia's Kurgan region, injuring seven seventh graders. The victims suffered bruises and scrapes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/russia-kurgan-school-shooting/29112975.html|title=Russian Schoolgirl Shoots Classmates With Gas Pistol, Seven Injured |date=March 21, 2018 |work=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|April 18, 2018}}\n|[[Sterlitamak]], Russia\n| Student\n|\n| 4 injured\n| Four people were hospitalized after a knife-wielding teenage student attacked his school in Russia's Bashkortostan region, in the city of Sterlitamak. The attacker wounded three girls and a teacher, and set a classroom on fire.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/three-students-teacher-hospitalized-after-teen-attacks-school-in-russia/29174568.html|title=Three Students, Teacher Hospitalized After Teen Attacks School In Russia |date=April 18, 2018 |work=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|April 20, 2018}}\n|[[Ocala, Florida]], United States\n| Sky Bouche, 19\n|\n| 1 injured\n| A former Forest High School student entered the school with a guitar case containing a 1930 sawed-off shotgun. He retrieved the gun in the washroom, and entered the hallway. Bouche was ready to fire and reportedly had seen multiple students, but had a strike of morality before firing. He later stated when the moment came, and he saw a female students distress in reaction to seeing him, he couldn't bring himself to hurt anyone. Instead he fired a shot at a nearby closed door, without aiming. He later claimed that he \"didn't think the gun would fire\". A 17-year-old male student in the classroom was wounded after he was shot in the ankle. Bouche then entered the classroom of one of his former teachers, and surrendered peacefully to the responding SRO. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ocala.com/news/20190420/one-year-after-shooting-at-ocalas-forest-high-school|title=One year after the shooting at Ocala\u2019s Forest High School |date=April 20, 2019 |work=OcalaStarBanner}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|April 27, 2018}}\n| [[Mizhi county]], [[Yulin]], [[Shaanxi]], China\n| Zhao Zewei, 28\n| 9 dead\n| 10 injured\n| Nine students were stabbed to death and 10 injured in a knife attack outside a school in northern China. The man who carried out the attack was reportedly a former student, taking revenge for having been bullied at the school. The dead were seven girls and two boys aged 12 to 15.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-43921567|title=China stabbings: Nine students killed in Shaanxi |date=April 28, 2018 |work=BBC News}}</ref>\n|-\n|May 25, 2018\n|[[Palmdale, California]], US\n| Student, 14\n| \n|1 injured\n|A 14 year old male opened fire with a rifle at roughly 7:00&nbsp;a.m. at [[Highland High School (Palmdale, California)|Highland High School]] campus and then walked into a bathroom. The shots wounded one former schoolmate, a male who was shot in his arm. The suspect shot 10 rounds. He then dumped the gun in a field before he was taken into custody in a nearby shopping center.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dailynews.com/2018/05/11/deputies-respond-to-report-of-man-with-a-gun-at-palmdales-highland-high-school//|title= Student shot at Highland High School in Palmdale, former schoolmate in custody |last=|first=|date=2018-05-18|work=CBS Interactive Inc.|access-date=2018-05-19|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|-\n|May 18, 2018\n|[[Santa Fe, Texas]], US\n|Dimitrios Pagourtzis, 17\n|10 dead\n|14 injured\n|[[Santa Fe High School shooting]]. A student armed with a shotgun and a .38 revolver smuggled under his coat opened fire on [[Santa Fe High School (Texas)|Santa Fe High School]] campus, killing 10 people and wounding 13 more, as well as injuring himself.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/18/us/school-shooting-santa-fe-texas.html|title=Texas School Shooting: 10 Dead, 10 Hurt, and Many Not Surprised It Happened|last=Fernandez|first=Manny|date=2018-05-18|work=The New York Times|access-date=2018-05-19|last2=Fausset|first2=Richard|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|last3=Bidgood|first3=Jess}}</ref>\n|-\n|May 25, 2018\n|[[Noblesville, Indiana]], US\n| Student, 13\n| \n|2 injured\n|[[Noblesville West Middle School shooting]]. A 13-year-old student opened fire at 9:06.<ref name=\"f59-what-we-know\">{{cite news|title=Here\u2019s what we know about the Noblesville West Middle School shooting that injured student, teacher|url=http://fox59.com/2018/05/25/heres-what-we-know-about-the-noblesville-west-middle-school-shooting/|accessdate=25 May 2018|agency=FOX59}}</ref> a.m. on [[Noblesville West Middle School]] campus, injuring two; an adult and a teenager. The shooter asked to be excused during a science test. He returned to the classroom with two handguns and fired at two people: a thirteen-year-old student; Ella Whistler and the assailant's science teacher. The science teacher, Jason Seaman, threw a basketball at the assailant before bear hugging and wrestling him to the ground, sustaining bullet wounds in the process. Students recounted that Seaman was yelling at the students to call 911, and to evacuate from the room. Seaman later stated that his actions were \"...the only acceptable actions I could have done given the circumstances.\" After the incident, the suspect came into custody.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/indiana-school-shooting-report-of-shots-fired-at-noblesville-west-middle-school/|title=Police: 2 injured in shooting at Noblesville West Middle School in Indiana|last=|first=|date=2018-05-18|work=CBS Interactive Inc.|access-date=2018-05-19|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|-\n|October 17, 2018\n|[[Kerch]]\n| Vladislav Roslyakov, 18\n|21 dead\n|70 injured\n|The [[Kerch Polytechnic College massacre]]. An 18-year-old student at the [[Kerch Polytechnic College]] set off explosives in the school and began shooting, killing 20. The shooter was highly inspired by the [[Columbine High School Massacre]], even going as far as wearing the same clothes as one of the two shooters involved in that attack.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-45891201|title=Gun attack at Crimea college kills 19|date=October 17, 2018|via=www.bbc.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|December 17, 2018\n|[[Haridwar, Uttarakhand]], India\n| Student, 13\n| -\n|1 injured\n| DAV Public School shooting in Haridwar\n|-\n|February 11, 2019\n|[[Stowbtsy]], Belarus\n| Vadim Miloshevsky, 15\n| 2 dead\n| 2 injured\n| 15-year-old student, Vadim Miloshevsky, stabbed a 50-year-old history teacher in the neck, who then died on the spot. He also stabbed two students, who tried to defend the teacher, injuring both of them. The assailant then left the class and entered a nearby classroom, where he stabbed a 17-year-old student, who also died on the spot.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/belarusian-teen-suspected-of-stabbing-teacher-classmate-to-death/29763228.html|title=Belarusian Teen Suspected Of Stabbing Teacher, Classmate To Death |date=February 11, 2019 |work=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty}}</ref>\n|-\n|February 26, 2019\n|[[Toronto]], Ontario\n| Unknown \n| \n| 2 injured\n| A fight between two students outside York Memorial Collegiate Institute ended off with a double stabbing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://toronto.citynews.ca/2019/02/26/stabbing-york-memorial-collegiate/|title=2 students stabbed outside York Memorial Collegiate Institute |date=February 26, 2019 |work=CityNews}}</ref>\n|-\n|March 13, 2019\n|[[Suzano]], Brazil\n| Guilherme Taucci Monteiro, 17; Luiz Henrique de Castro, 25\n| 10 dead\n| 11 injured\n| [[Suzano massacre|Two masked]] men shot and killed 6 students and 2 staff members at a public secondary school in Suzano, Brazil. Eleven additional victims were wounded. The suspects committed suicide inside the school.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/03/13/americas/brazil-school-shooting/index.html/|title=At least 8 people were killed in a school shooting in Brazil |date=March 13, 2019 |work=CNN}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 7, 2019\n| Colorado, United States\n| Devon Erickson, 18; Alec Elizabeth, 16\n| 1 dead\n| 8 injured\n| At the [[STEM School Highlands Ranch]] two suspects, who were students at the school, injured eight students and killed one.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/05/08/us/denver-stem-shooting-heroes-run-hide-fight/index.html|title=Again in the age of 'run, hide, fight,' student heroes thwart a school shooter|first=Eliott C.|last= McLaughlin|website=CNN}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/05/08/us/kendrick-castillo-denver-stem-shooting/index.html|title=This student died trying to stop the Colorado school shooter|author1=Nicole Chavez |author2=Scott McLean|website=CNN}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 27, 2019\n| [[Puerto Montt]], [[Los Lagos]], [[Chile]]\n| Student\n| \n| 1 injured\n| That Monday morning, a 14-year-old student was shot and injured by fellow student at Patagonia College, in a targeted attack. The attack was done with a gun the shooter had stole from his grandfather. The gunman walked into the school wearing a military jacket, and a mask from the Netflix show Money Heist. The shooter fled the school, and left the gun in a canal nearby the school. The victim was rushed to a hospital. The shooter was later arrested. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://https://www.biobiochile.cl/noticias/biobiochile-english/english-chile/2019/05/27/school-shooting-leaves-one-minor-injured-in-southern-chile.shtml |title= School shooting leaves one minor injured in southern Chile |date=27 May 2019 | website=BioBioChile}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url= https://chiletoday.cl/site/editorial-school-incidents-as-bait-to-promote-government-control/ |title=Editorial: School Incidents As Bait To Promote Government Control |author=Boris van der Spek |website=ChileToday |date=May 28, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 28, 2019\n| [[Volsk]], [[Saratov Region]], Russia\n| Daniil Pulkin\n| \n| 1 injured\n| In the afternoon of May 28, the teenager came to school with a bag containing an axe and molotov cocktails inside. First, Pulkin attempted to burn the office of his former form mistress. After that, he hit a 6th grader girl in the head with an axe.\n|-\n| August 30, 2019\n| Mobile, Alabama\n| Deangelo Dejuan Parnell, 17\n| \n| 10 injured\n| Parnell shot 9 people during a confrontation at a stadium where a high school football game was being played. A tenth person suffered a stroke.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/31/us/mobile-alabama-football-shooting.html|title=At Least 10 Shot at Alabama High School Football Game, Police Say|first=Derrick Bryson|last=Taylor|date=August 31, 2019|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 1, 2019\n| [[Kuopio]], Finland\n| Joel Marin, 25\n| 1 dead\n| 10 injured\n| [[Kuopio school stabbing]]\n|-\n| November 14, 2019 \n| Santa Clarita, California\n| Nathaniel Berhow, 16\n| 3 dead\n| 3 injured \n| [[Saugus High School shooting]]\n|-\n| November 14, 2019\n| [[Blagoveshchensk]], Russia\n| Daniil Zasorin, 19\n| 3 dead\n| 2 injured\n| After being told to leave the classroom twice, Zasorin returned with a pump-action shotgun and opened fire in the room, shooting victims at their desks. He committed suicide after being wounded in exchange of gunfire with police.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/russia-college-shooting-daniil-zasorin-attack-death-toll-latest-today-a9202526.html|title=Gunman opens fire in deadly Russian college attack after posting bizarre message online|date=14 November 2019|website=The Independent|accessdate=10 January 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===2020s===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:65px;\"| Date\n! style=\"width:85px;\"| Location\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Attacker(s)\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" style=\"width:75px;\"| Dead{{r|group=lower-alpha|note_a}}\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" style=\"width:75px;\"| Injured{{r|group=lower-alpha|note_a}}\n! Description\n|-\n| January 11, 2020\n| [[Dallas]], [[Texas]], [[United States]]\n| Suspect, 15\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured \n| A 15-year-old was been arrested after two people were wounded by gunfire during a fight at a high school basketball game between South Oak Cliff and Kimball High Schools. An 18-year-old man was badly wounded in the shooting, and a Dallas ISD police officer was grazed by a bullet fragment. The 15-year-old suspect, who turned himself in at Dallas police headquarters, was at first charged with aggravated assault. However, the 18-year-old student died from his injuries so the suspect is now being charged with murder.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dallasnews.com/news/crime/2020/01/12/2-wounded-in-shooting-at-high-school-basketball-game-in-dallas-police-say/ |title= 15-year-old arrested in shooting at South Oak Cliff-Kimball basketball game that wounded 2, Dallas police say |date=12 January 2020 |website=Dallas News}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/teen-facing-murder-charge-victim-shot-dallas-high/story?id=68385916 |title=Teen facing murder charge after victim shot at Dallas high school basketball game dies |date=19 January 2020 |website=ABC News}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 14, 2020\n| [[Fort Worth]], Texas, United States\n| Unknown suspect\n| \n| 2 injured \n| An adult male and a 10-year-old child were injured in a North Crowley Ninth Grade Campus parking lot. The incident occurred around 7 p.m., after a youth basketball game. Fort Worth police say the incident occurred after a suspect, who was damaging a car in the parking lot, was confronted. The suspect then shot the man and a child. An ambulance took the man to John Peter Smith Hospital, while the 10-year-old was taken to Cook Children's Hospital in a private vehicle. The boy was expected to undergo surgery, possibly to retrieve a projectile. The game was not a school-sponsored event. The shooting also did not involve any  students. The facility was often rented for community sporting events, and was rented by a youth organization in the case here.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wfaa.com/article/news/local/1-person-shot-at-parking-lot-of-school-campus-in-fort-worth-police-say/287-1bc57cb9-271c-4a57-bbfc-6fb21b9c4009 |title= 2 injured in shooting at school parking lot, Fort Worth police say |date=19 January 2020 |website=WFAA}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbcdfw.com/news/local/1-critically-injured-in-shooting-after-youth-basketball-game/2294920/ |title= Adult, 10-Year-Old Injured in Shooting Outside Youth Basketball Game, Police Say |date=20 January 2020|website=NBC News}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[School bullying]]\n*[[School shooting]]\n*[[List of school-related attacks]]\n*[[List of school shootings in the United States]]\n*[[List of attacks related to primary schools]]\n*[[List of attacks related to post-secondary schools]]\n*[[List of rampage killers: School massacres]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist|refs=\n<ref name=note_a>Including death or injury of attacker(s), when applicable.</ref>}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181140/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence00-01.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2000\u20132001], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181216/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence02-03.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2002\u20132003], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181239/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence04-05.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2004\u20132005], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181347/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence06-07.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2006\u20132007], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181441/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence07-08.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2007\u20132008], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181632/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence08-09.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2008\u20132009], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181945/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence09-10.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2009\u20132010], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:School-Related Attacks}}\n[[Category:Attacks on schools|*]]\n[[Category:Lists of schools|*]]\n[[Category:Crime-related lists]]\n[[Category:Secondary education-related lists]]\n[[Category:Lists of school-related attacks|secondary]]\n", "name_user": "BorderRegions", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200e1930s", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_attacks_related_to_secondary_schools"}
{"title_page": "The Flintstone Comedy Show", "text_new": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = The Flintstone Comedy Show\n| image                = Hanna-Barbera 0016.jpg\n| genre                = [[Animation]], [[Comedy]]\n| camera               =\n| picture_format       =\n| runtime              = 90 minutes (1980\u201381)<br>60 minutes (1981)\n| creator              =\n| writer               = \n| director             = [[Ray Patterson (animator)|Ray Patterson]]<br>[[George Gordon (animator)|George Gordon]]<br>[[Rudy Zamora]]\n| producer             = [[Alex Lovy]]<br>[[Carl Urbano]]\n| executive_producer   = [[William Hanna]]<br>[[Joseph Barbera]]\n| composer             = [[Hoyt Curtin]]\n| starring             =\n| voices               = [[Gay Autterson]]<br>[[Mel Blanc]]<br>[[Henry Corden]]<br>[[Ruta Lee]]<br>[[Kenneth Mars]]<br>[[Mitzi McCall]]<br>[[Don Messick]]<br>[[Charles Nelson Reilly]]<br>[[Paul Reubens]]<br>[[Zelda Rubinstein]]<br>[[Michael Sheehan (actor)|Michael Sheehan]]<br>[[John Stephenson (actor)|John Stephenson]]<br>[[Russi Taylor]]<br>[[Jean Vander Pyl]]<br>[[Lennie Weinrib]]<br>[[Frank Welker]]\n| narrated             = [[Kenneth Mars]] (\"Captain Caveman\" segments)\n| theme_music_composer = [[Hoyt Curtin]]\n| company              = [[Hanna-Barbera|Hanna-Barbera Productions]]\n| distributor = [[Turner Program Services]] (1992\u201396){{Plainlist}}[[Warner Bros. Television Distribution]] (1996\u2013present)\n| opentheme            =\n| endtheme             =\n| country              = United States\n| language             = English\n| network              = [[NBC]]\n| audio_format         = [[Monaural]]\n| first_aired          = {{start date|1980|11|22}}\n| last_aired           = {{end date|1981|10|24}}\n| num_seasons          = 2\n| num_episodes         = 18\n| list_episodes        =\n| preceded_by          = ''[[Fred and Barney Meet the Shmoo]]''\n| followed_by          = ''[[The Flintstone Funnies]]''\n| related              =\n| website              =\n}}\n'''''The Flintstone Comedy Show''''' (not to be confused with the shortened, re-titled 1973 version of CBS's ''[[The Flintstone Comedy Hour]]'') is an American [[Saturday-morning cartoon|animated television series]] revival and [[spin-off (media)|spin-off]] of ''[[The Flintstones]]'' produced by [[Hanna-Barbera]] which aired on [[NBC]] from November 22, 1980  to October 24, 1981.<ref name=Perlmutter>{{cite book |last1=Perlmutter |first1=David |title=The Encyclopedia of American Animated Television Shows |date=2018 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-1538103739 |pages=209-214}}</ref> Outside [[North America]], the show was released under title of ''Flintstone Frolics''. The show contained six segments: ''The Flintstone Family Adventures'', ''Bedrock Cops'', ''Pebbles, Dino and Bamm-Bamm'', ''Captain Caveman'', ''Dino and Cavemouse'' and ''The Frankenstones''.<ref name=Woolery>{{cite book |last1=Woolery |first1=George W. |title=Children's Television: The First Thirty-Five Years, 1946-1981 |date=1983 |publisher=Scarecrow Press |isbn=0-8108-1557-5  |url=https://archive.org/details/childrenstelevis0000wool/page/106/mode/2up |accessdate=14 March 2020 |pages=106-109}}</ref>\n\n==Overview==\nThe series featured new characters ([[The Frankenstones]], Cavemouse) as well as older characters (Penny, Wiggy, Moonrock and Schleprock of 1971's ''[[The Pebbles and Bamm-Bamm Show]]'' and 1972's ''[[The Flintstone Comedy Hour]]'' on [[CBS]], [[Al Capp]]'s the [[Shmoo]] from his show ''[[The New Shmoo]]'' which also aired on [[NBC]] in 1979, [[Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels|Captain Caveman]] from his own series on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] in 1977 which lasted 3 seasons).\n\nA series of gags, educational spots, games, how-to-draw and a dance-of-the-week were featured in-between the six segments every week. In [[1982 in television|1982]], reruns of the show were repackaged for two seasons under the title '''''[[The Flintstone Funnies]]'''''. Reruns of \"Dino and Cavemouse\" aired on the [[Disney Channel]] adaption of ''[[Wake, Rattle, and Roll]]''.\n\n==Segments==\n\n===The Flintstone Family Adventures===\nThis segment featured the traditional antics and adventures of The Flintstones and The Rubbles.\n\n====Season 1 (1980\u201381)====\n{| class=wikitable style=\"background:#FFFFFF\"\n! style=\"background:#FF681F; width:20px\"| {{Abbr|N\u00ba|Number}}\n! style=\"background:#FF681F; width:20px\"| {{Abbr|Ep|Episode}}\n! style=\"background:#FF681F\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#FF681F; width:135px\"| Original air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 1\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 1\n| Title               = R.V. Fever\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|11|22}}\n| ShortSummary        = As the Flintstones and the Rubbles take a road trip, the R.V. trailer with Fred and Barney comes unhitched.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 2\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 2\n| Title               = Sands of the Saharastone\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|11|29}}\n| ShortSummary        = The Flintstones and the Rubbles take a trip to Algeristone where Wilma and Betty are abducted by sheiks to add to their harems.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 3\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 3\n| Title               = Gold Fever\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|12|6}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred and Barney go on a trip to the Bedrock Mountains to search for gold until some claim jumpers try to capture them.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 4\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 4\n| Title               = Bogged Down\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|12|13}}\n| ShortSummary        = After Barney sells a dilapidated resort that he inherited from his uncle, Fred discovers oil on the property.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 5\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 5\n| Title               = Be Patient, Fred\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|12|20}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred goes to the hospital to get his tonsils removed, but things go awry when Fred is mixed up with another patient who is scheduled to have surgery.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 6\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 6\n| Title               = Country Club Clods\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|12|27}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred introduces the Frankenstones to the Bedrock Country Club, but soon regrets it when they wreak havoc and terror.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 7\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 7\n| Title               = The Rockdale Diet\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|1|3}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred attempts to lose weight by following the Rockdale Diet and Wilma carefully monitors his every sneaky scheme to eat.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 8\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 8\n| Title               = Dino's Girl\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|1|10}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred unwittingly brings home Mr. Slate's pet dinosaur Dina and soon discovers that Dino is in love with her.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 9\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 9\n| Title               = The Gourmet Dinner\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|1|17}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred and Wilma invite Mr. and Mrs. Slate to accompany them to Frankenstone's house for a gourmet meal.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 10\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 10\n| Title               = The Stand-In\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|1|24}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred and Wilma are hired as stands-ins for their favorite stars when the actors arrive in Bedrock to film a new movie.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 11\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 11\n| Title               = Go Take a Hike\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|1|31}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred and Barney take a turbulent hike to the mountains with Pebbles, Bamm-Bamm, Moonrock and the Frankenstone kids.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n|} \n\n====Season 2 (1981\u201382)====\n{| class=wikitable style=\"background:#FFFFFF\"\n! style=\"background:#FF681F; width:20px\"| {{Abbr|N\u00ba|Number}}\n! style=\"background:#FF681F; width:20px\"| {{Abbr|Ep|Episode}}\n! style=\"background:#FF681F\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#FF681F; width:135px\"| Original air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 12\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 1\n| Title               = The Great Bedrock Air Race\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|9|12}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred and Barney assemble Mr. Slate's new \"Aerosubmabus\" to enter in the Great Bedrock Air Race.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 13\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 2\n| Title               = Fred's Last Resort\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|9|19}}\n| ShortSummary        = A visit to a health spa turns into a nightmare for Fred when he endures a vigorous massage and a workout at the gym.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 14\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 3\n| Title               = The Not-Such-A-Pleasure Cruise\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|9|26}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred is looking forward to a peaceful cruise, but the vacation turns into a disaster when he encounters pirates.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 15\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 4\n| Title               = Fred's Big Top Flop\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|10|3}}\n| ShortSummary        = The Flintstones and the Rubbles perform in the circus after Fred is mistaken for \"The Flying Flintstonis\